text: Come on Over is an album released by country music singer Shania Twain. It was released in 1997. It is the biggest selling album by a female country singer. All of the songs were written by Shania Twain and Mutt Lange. Singles released off of the album include the title track, "That Don't Impress Me Much", "Man! I Feel Like A Woman!", "Honey, I'm Home", "You're Still The One", "From This Moment On", "You've Got A Way", "Love Gets Me Every Time," "Don't Be Stupid!", "When", "Rock This Country!", and "I'm Holding On To Love (To Save My Life)".
